1
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,480
Show your face!

2
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:33,400
PREVIOUS EPISODE

3
00:02:33,480 --> 00:02:34,400
Boss.

4
00:02:35,560 --> 00:02:36,520
They're here.

5
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:37,680
Is everyone ready?

6
00:02:37,760 --> 00:02:38,800
Yes.

7
00:02:38,880 --> 00:02:39,880
Hey! Are you trying to run?

8
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:43,040
Just wait, Singha. One day,

9
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:45,960
I'll rip that mask off of you.

10
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:47,400
Definitely a pervert.

11
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:51,000
MEN'S RESTROOM

12
00:02:51,880 --> 00:02:52,800
It's fine.

13
00:02:52,880 --> 00:02:54,720
We don't need any money.

14
00:02:56,360 --> 00:02:57,760
Just say what you want.

15
00:02:57,840 --> 00:03:01,680
In that case, a different kind of reward
would be better.

16
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:07,120
I heard there was a shooting
and even an explosion.

17
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:10,320
Go ahead and turn your phone on.

18
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:13,280
Call Aunt Wilai and Teacher Mueangphrai.
They're both worried.

19
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:08,080
<i>Why does this embrace feel so warm?</i>

20
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:15,440
<i>I feel safe.</i>

21
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:19,440
<i>It's like I'm a little bird</i>
<i>under my mother's wing.</i>

22
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:25,000
<i>What would my mother's embrace feel like?</i>

23
00:04:26,280 --> 00:04:28,080
<i>Would it make me</i>

24
00:04:29,440 --> 00:04:31,320
<i>feel this warm too?</i>

25
00:04:46,680 --> 00:04:49,200
I'm sorry for making you worry.

26
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:52,320
It's okay.

27
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:54,880
You didn't do anything wrong.

28
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:59,000
But next time,

29
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:01,680
don't go anywhere alone, okay?

30
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:04,640
At Khok Ta Yu village,

31
00:05:05,160 --> 00:05:07,880
there's hidden danger,
things we can't see.

32
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:13,840
And promise me,

33
00:05:15,320 --> 00:05:17,440
you won't be stubborn with Uncle Tharin.

34
00:05:17,960 --> 00:05:19,840
You'll listen to him.

35
00:05:24,080 --> 00:05:25,800
I promise.

36
00:05:28,520 --> 00:05:30,720
I had to bring Wilai here,

37
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:32,520
or she'd still be worrying
for many more days.

38
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:37,120
Are you feeling better now, Wilai?

39
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:40,080
Yes, thank you.

40
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:46,720
Let's head back now.

41
00:05:49,920 --> 00:05:50,960
I'm leaving, Poona.

42
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,120
Goodbye, Teacher.

43
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:01,120
Goodbye, Aunt Wilai.

44
00:06:04,160 --> 00:06:05,840
<i>It's strange.</i>

45
00:06:07,080 --> 00:06:10,040
<i>Why don't I want Aunt Wilai to leave?</i>

46
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:39,320
I'll go now.

47
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:36,360
Aunt Wilai.

48
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:49,800
We only collected this much today.
We're short on five accounts.

49
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:51,760
What the hell?

50
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:53,280
Five accounts short?

51
00:07:53,880 --> 00:07:55,400
Which vendors dared

52
00:07:55,480 --> 00:07:58,800
to skip their payments?
If they can't afford to pay back,

53
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:02,920
make them pay with their lives. Got it?

54
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:06,720
Hey, Euang.

55
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:08,720
Where are you? Come out here!

56
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:11,720
Hey, no need to hide.

57
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:13,680
Do you want us to break in?

58
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:17,560
I'm giving you time, from one to five.

59
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:20,440
Are you gonna come out?

60
00:08:21,880 --> 00:08:22,840
One.

61
00:08:24,920 --> 00:08:25,800
Two.

62
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:28,560
Three.

63
00:08:29,960 --> 00:08:31,800
- Four.
- Okay, okay.

64
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:33,520
Okay, I'm coming!

65
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:35,840
Here I am.

66
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:40,400
Finally, we meet, Auntie.
You've been hiding for so long.

67
00:08:42,039 --> 00:08:43,840
I'm not feeling well.

68
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:46,240
Not feeling well?

69
00:08:46,760 --> 00:08:49,120
Doesn't matter. You still need to pay.

70
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:50,800
You've missed three days.

71
00:08:51,520 --> 00:08:53,760
That's 1,500 in total. Pay up.

72
00:08:57,880 --> 00:09:00,480
- I only have this much.
- Two hundred?

73
00:09:01,480 --> 00:09:02,520
- Hey, Auntie.
- Yes?

74
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:04,560
Don't play tricks with me.

75
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:10,280
Chaiya, look over there.

76
00:09:12,320 --> 00:09:15,400
Get the 1,300 now.

77
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:18,760
I'm not feeling well. Please,
have some pity. I'm really sick.

78
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:21,760
- Oh yeah?
- Yes.

79
00:09:24,560 --> 00:09:27,040
- Auntie, are you really that sick?
- Yes?

80
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:31,600
Don't!

81
00:09:32,880 --> 00:09:33,920
They're hurting the elder.

82
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,720
No. Look over there.

83
00:09:35,800 --> 00:09:37,080
Hey, stop right there!

84
00:09:40,560 --> 00:09:42,400
Mr. Singha!

85
00:09:42,480 --> 00:09:45,920
I'm really not well.
I really can't earn the money.

86
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:49,120
You're in debt,
so you have to pay. Understand?

87
00:09:49,720 --> 00:09:52,280
I'm really sick. Please have pity on me.

88
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:54,520
Fine. Hey.

89
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:58,000
Go inside and check.
Bring out anything valuable.

90
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:59,440
- Yes, sir.
- Got it.

91
00:10:12,280 --> 00:10:13,880
Please…

92
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:16,280
Please don't take my stuff.

93
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:20,400
This TV is worth more than 1,500!

94
00:10:21,800 --> 00:10:24,160
But I've only valued it at 1,500.

95
00:10:24,240 --> 00:10:27,480
If you're not happy, bring me the money.
What do you want to do?

96
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:29,880
I really can't get it.

97
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:33,080
I've tried borrowing,
but no one will lend me any.

98
00:10:35,160 --> 00:10:37,000
Then shut up.

99
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:52,160
Please don't take my stuff.
I'll sell it and give you the money back.

100
00:10:52,240 --> 00:10:55,040
Why didn't you just pay up
from the start, huh?

101
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:59,600
- Enough. Let's go.
- Yes, Boss.

102
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:03,120
Next time, it'll be worse!

103
00:11:04,560 --> 00:11:06,400
You're so cruel.

104
00:11:08,640 --> 00:11:11,440
This is another of Singha's businesses.

105
00:11:11,520 --> 00:11:14,640
He lends money and exploits the villagers.

106
00:11:15,520 --> 00:11:16,680
Why aren't the police doing anything?

107
00:11:17,280 --> 00:11:19,640
The profits are too tempting.
They can't act on it.

108
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:23,840
This has to be reported.
We can't just let it go.

109
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:26,400
People have reported it already,
but the case went quiet.

110
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:30,360
What about the villagers?
Aren't they doing anything?

111
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:32,400
Of course they've tried.
Someone secretly filmed it

112
00:11:32,480 --> 00:11:36,400
and reported it to the media.
The next day, he was brutally beaten.

113
00:11:36,480 --> 00:11:40,120
After that, no one dared
to do anything again.

114
00:11:43,040 --> 00:11:44,040
In that case,

115
00:11:44,800 --> 00:11:47,360
we'll have to pull them out by the roots.

116
00:11:49,280 --> 00:11:51,000
So the villagers can live in peace.

117
00:12:05,200 --> 00:12:06,720
Hey, what's up with you now?

118
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:08,840
I've become paranoid.

119
00:12:08,920 --> 00:12:10,400
Whenever bad guys show up

120
00:12:10,480 --> 00:12:13,120
to steal something,
there's always a hero who appears, right?

121
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,240
So I'm just paranoid.

122
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:16,360
- You're really paranoid.
- It's nothing. Let's go.

123
00:12:19,360 --> 00:12:21,280
Hey, see? I knew it.

124
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:22,960
Who are you guys?

125
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:27,760
- You want to get hurt or what?
- We're thieves.

126
00:12:29,120 --> 00:12:30,680
Wow, thieves?

127
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:33,600
Since when do thieves
talk so nicely and sweetly?

128
00:12:34,560 --> 00:12:36,400
How long have you been thieves?

129
00:12:36,480 --> 00:12:39,920
Or are you just rookie thieves?

130
00:12:40,520 --> 00:12:44,160
Hey, we're top-tier thieves.

131
00:12:44,240 --> 00:12:49,400
You, a rookie, want to train with us?
We're the veterans here.

132
00:12:50,680 --> 00:12:54,120
How long have you been a thief?

133
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:55,800
Just recently.

134
00:12:55,880 --> 00:12:57,840
When we saw you guys
robbing the villagers,

135
00:12:58,360 --> 00:13:00,120
we thought we'd give it a try too.

136
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:02,200
- That's interesting.
- Yeah.

137
00:13:03,320 --> 00:13:04,160
What's wrong with you guys?

138
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:09,240
- Are you mocking us?
- Yeah?

139
00:13:09,320 --> 00:13:10,920
Beat them up!

140
00:14:22,640 --> 00:14:27,720
DARATHONG MUSIC

141
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:37,280
Well.

142
00:14:38,120 --> 00:14:40,040
Is this what you two want?

143
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:44,360
Yes, this is it.

144
00:14:44,440 --> 00:14:45,800
This is our dream.

145
00:14:46,440 --> 00:14:49,520
We've dreamed for a long time
of working with Darathong Music.

146
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:54,880
Please let us work here.

147
00:14:55,760 --> 00:14:56,680
Please.

148
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:59,520
Something feels off.

149
00:15:00,680 --> 00:15:04,440
I think those two
might be hiding something.

150
00:15:07,680 --> 00:15:09,800
Then tell me.

151
00:15:10,320 --> 00:15:13,040
Why do you two want to work here?

152
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:17,680
I mean,

153
00:15:17,760 --> 00:15:21,760
we want to work with a talented YouTuber
like you, Mr. Sornrak.

154
00:15:21,840 --> 00:15:23,040
Exactly.

155
00:15:23,120 --> 00:15:26,640
You're my idol, Mr. Sornrak.
Learning from someone skilled is awesome.

156
00:15:27,360 --> 00:15:28,320
Right?

157
00:15:29,320 --> 00:15:30,320
Sure.

158
00:15:31,040 --> 00:15:33,360
Then, Manat.

159
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:38,160
You'll be my administrator and manage
my schedule. Can you do that?

160
00:15:38,240 --> 00:15:39,320
I can do it.

161
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:41,920
And you, Chaiya.

162
00:15:42,880 --> 00:15:46,840
You'll be my assistant,
following me everywhere I go.

163
00:15:46,920 --> 00:15:50,760
And both of you need to protect me.

164
00:15:52,040 --> 00:15:55,240
I'll be both an assistant
and a bodyguard, right?

165
00:15:55,880 --> 00:15:56,840
Exactly.

166
00:15:58,680 --> 00:16:01,400
Boss, isn't that my job?

167
00:16:02,160 --> 00:16:05,000
Your job? When it's time to step up,

168
00:16:05,680 --> 00:16:08,240
you've never helped me with anything.

169
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:10,600
You're lucky I haven't fired you yet.

170
00:16:11,360 --> 00:16:13,760
Alright, you can help Chaiya
with his work.

171
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:26,720
I look forward to working with you, Chang.

172
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:28,880
No need for that.

173
00:16:28,960 --> 00:16:31,000
Alright, got it.

174
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:44,880
Take it easy.

175
00:16:45,920 --> 00:16:47,880
- Hello.
- Hello.

176
00:16:47,960 --> 00:16:50,080
I think we've met before, right?

177
00:16:50,160 --> 00:16:52,640
Yes, from now on,
we'll be seeing each other more often.

178
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:09,040
What's up?

179
00:17:09,119 --> 00:17:11,960
Sornrak's out of the hospital, Boss.

180
00:17:12,040 --> 00:17:13,440
<i>Let him relax for now.</i>

181
00:17:14,040 --> 00:17:16,520
We'll wait for the right moment
and hit him again.

182
00:17:17,640 --> 00:17:20,119
Got it, Boss. I'll handle it.

183
00:17:31,040 --> 00:17:33,880
DARATHONG MUSIC

184
00:17:37,680 --> 00:17:39,040
MARIA DARATHONG, SORNRAK DARATHONG

185
00:17:42,040 --> 00:17:43,400
Isn't that Maria?

186
00:17:45,840 --> 00:17:46,760
Yeah.

187
00:17:46,840 --> 00:17:48,880
Maria's a singer now?

188
00:17:50,120 --> 00:17:53,400
You two, go wait for me
in the conference room.

189
00:17:53,480 --> 00:17:54,680
I've got work to discuss.

190
00:17:54,760 --> 00:17:55,880
- Got it.
- Got it.

191
00:18:06,120 --> 00:18:07,640
Who are those two guys?

192
00:18:08,240 --> 00:18:09,920
They're Mr. Sornrak's new assistants.

193
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:11,480
They're so handsome.

194
00:18:12,440 --> 00:18:14,720
- Who are they?
- Mr. Sornrak's new assistants.

195
00:18:15,320 --> 00:18:17,880
Two new ones,
and they're definitely model material.

196
00:18:18,960 --> 00:18:20,680
Model material?

197
00:18:20,760 --> 00:18:23,840
They're top-tier, rare and premium.

198
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:28,720
Wait a minute. Can you translate that?
I don't understand.

199
00:18:29,440 --> 00:18:31,200
Why don't you ask AI, sis?

200
00:18:33,440 --> 00:18:36,680
How would I know who AI is?
This building is full of people.

201
00:18:37,320 --> 00:18:38,440
Wait!

202
00:18:39,520 --> 00:18:40,680
Who's AI?

203
00:18:46,280 --> 00:18:48,440
Model material, huh?

204
00:18:55,040 --> 00:18:57,480
This is my schedule.

205
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:00,800
From now on, you two will be in charge.

206
00:19:02,560 --> 00:19:04,520
Make sure I stick to my schedule.

207
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:10,840
This is the company phone.
You'll be answering calls,

208
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:14,440
handling business calls
or anyone else who calls.

209
00:19:14,960 --> 00:19:16,080
You can do that, right?

210
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:18,400
Yes.

211
00:19:21,960 --> 00:19:22,800
Any questions?

212
00:19:22,880 --> 00:19:25,240
Can I ask something off-topic?

213
00:19:25,320 --> 00:19:26,440
Go ahead.

214
00:19:26,520 --> 00:19:30,800
Maria came in second place.
Why is she a singer before the winner?

215
00:19:34,440 --> 00:19:36,600
That's none of your business.
Why are you asking?

216
00:19:37,800 --> 00:19:39,480
That's part of management.

217
00:19:42,240 --> 00:19:44,040
Just focus on your job.

218
00:20:03,520 --> 00:20:09,360
<i>Back then, my heart was strong</i>

219
00:20:11,040 --> 00:20:17,360
<i>As tough as a bar of steel</i>

220
00:20:18,240 --> 00:20:23,360
<i>So many men chased after me</i>

221
00:20:23,440 --> 00:20:26,480
<i>But I never paid them any mind</i>

222
00:20:27,080 --> 00:20:31,880
<i>Never gave them a thought</i>

223
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:37,400
<i>But now, my heart is starting to weaken</i>

224
00:20:39,080 --> 00:20:45,800
<i>From the very first time I saw him</i>
<i>My heart started to waver</i>

225
00:20:46,320 --> 00:20:50,760
<i>What is it about this man?</i>

226
00:20:50,840 --> 00:20:54,240
<i>Every time I see his face</i>

227
00:20:54,320 --> 00:20:59,600
<i>My heart pounds</i>

228
00:20:59,680 --> 00:21:00,880
<i>Oh, my heart--</i>

229
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:03,880
Hey, it's me!

230
00:21:07,480 --> 00:21:08,720
You pervert!

231
00:21:09,760 --> 00:21:10,960
Hey, you.

232
00:21:11,040 --> 00:21:13,040
You're calling me a pervert? Just wait!

233
00:21:14,080 --> 00:21:17,960
Isn't it true?
I saw you by the bathroom that day.

234
00:21:19,880 --> 00:21:21,080
Think what you want.

235
00:21:22,480 --> 00:21:23,640
Forget it.

236
00:21:24,240 --> 00:21:25,800
What are you doing here?

237
00:21:26,840 --> 00:21:27,680
I'm here for work.

238
00:21:28,760 --> 00:21:29,960
Work?

239
00:21:30,040 --> 00:21:32,200
Yeah, work.

240
00:21:32,720 --> 00:21:35,480
You work here?
How come I didn't know about this?

241
00:21:37,360 --> 00:21:40,720
It's a long story. I'll tell you later.

242
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:44,520
But what about you?

243
00:21:44,600 --> 00:21:47,520
You won first place
in the singing contest.

244
00:21:47,600 --> 00:21:50,360
Why are you here hanging laundry?

245
00:21:52,760 --> 00:21:55,840
What's wrong? Did you get cheated on?

246
00:22:06,680 --> 00:22:07,720
Hey.

247
00:22:08,920 --> 00:22:09,920
Hey.

248
00:22:10,560 --> 00:22:14,160
I didn't mean to say it like that.

249
00:22:15,440 --> 00:22:16,440
Well…

250
00:22:19,160 --> 00:22:21,760
Hey, hey. Hey!

251
00:22:29,520 --> 00:22:31,600
Hey! Hey!

252
00:22:32,480 --> 00:22:33,440
Wait up.

253
00:22:51,240 --> 00:22:52,840
Are you crying?

254
00:22:56,640 --> 00:22:57,880
If there's nothing else,

255
00:22:58,440 --> 00:23:00,280
you can go back to work.

256
00:23:03,480 --> 00:23:04,640
I have to go.

257
00:23:30,160 --> 00:23:31,600
Let's take a break!

258
00:23:32,400 --> 00:23:34,800
Miss Maria's tired, Teacher.

259
00:23:35,320 --> 00:23:37,120
We haven't practiced for half an hour yet.

260
00:23:37,200 --> 00:23:39,280
Come on, Teacher.

261
00:23:39,360 --> 00:23:41,880
Miss Maria's already great.
She knows how to dance. She's good.

262
00:23:41,960 --> 00:23:44,440
- Let's take a break for a bit.
- Okay, sure.

263
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:46,360
Thank you.

264
00:23:46,440 --> 00:23:48,920
Joey, come on. Joey.

265
00:23:51,320 --> 00:23:53,800
- I told you to come here!
- Okay.

266
00:23:57,920 --> 00:24:00,680
What is it, Sophie?
Why did you drag me out?

267
00:24:00,760 --> 00:24:02,760
Breaking news! Big news, Miss Maria!

268
00:24:02,840 --> 00:24:04,440
What? What news?

269
00:24:04,520 --> 00:24:06,400
I overheard the staff gossiping.

270
00:24:06,480 --> 00:24:09,520
Mr. Sornrak has hired new assistants,
and they're super hot.

271
00:24:09,600 --> 00:24:11,360
And it's a duo package!

272
00:24:11,440 --> 00:24:12,520
What's the big deal?

273
00:24:13,520 --> 00:24:16,800
We should get close to them.
They're assistants, right?

274
00:24:16,880 --> 00:24:19,240
It'll be useful for us.

275
00:24:19,320 --> 00:24:21,600
How's that useful?

276
00:24:21,680 --> 00:24:25,080
Listen, the assistant
knows the boss's schedule.

277
00:24:25,160 --> 00:24:27,640
So, Mr. Sornrak's assistants
will obviously know his schedule.

278
00:24:27,720 --> 00:24:30,040
Of course. Yeah.

279
00:24:30,120 --> 00:24:33,680
Miss Maria, you'll get closer
to Mr. Sornrak and rise with him.

280
00:24:33,760 --> 00:24:37,440
Exactly! When we went to donate,
the buzz was incredible.

281
00:24:37,520 --> 00:24:38,920
Yeah!

282
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:42,600
Your Instagram followers
have gone up by 10,000.

283
00:24:43,440 --> 00:24:46,120
That's why we need
to get close to his assistants.

284
00:24:46,200 --> 00:24:49,400
- So we can know his schedule, right?
- Right.

285
00:24:52,960 --> 00:24:54,600
Hey, who's that?

286
00:24:55,640 --> 00:24:59,480
Is that Mr. Sornrak's assistant? That guy!

287
00:25:00,360 --> 00:25:01,960
Oh my, I'm shocked by those muscles!

288
00:25:05,120 --> 00:25:07,800
Hey, wait. Hold it together.

289
00:25:07,880 --> 00:25:09,280
You're drooling.

290
00:25:09,360 --> 00:25:13,760
I can't handle it. I can be tired,
but a man should never be!

291
00:25:14,960 --> 00:25:18,480
Dear! Dear!

292
00:25:18,560 --> 00:25:20,040
Dear!

293
00:25:20,120 --> 00:25:23,200
Is it heavy? Need help with that?

294
00:25:23,280 --> 00:25:25,360
- Sure.
- Okay.

295
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:30,200
Sorry, I forgot to mention it's heavy.

296
00:25:30,280 --> 00:25:31,760
It's fine, kid.

297
00:25:32,600 --> 00:25:35,560
I used to work as a laborer.

298
00:25:37,720 --> 00:25:39,240
Are you okay?

299
00:25:50,520 --> 00:25:51,480
You!

300
00:26:28,520 --> 00:26:31,040
CONTROL ROOM

301
00:26:50,880 --> 00:26:52,240
Do you need something from me?

302
00:26:52,320 --> 00:26:55,120
I was just curious,
why are you working here?

303
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:57,640
Why were you heading
into the men's restroom?

304
00:26:57,720 --> 00:26:58,920
Oh!

305
00:27:00,000 --> 00:27:03,320
I thought it was the women's restroom.
I didn't see the sign.

306
00:27:04,200 --> 00:27:05,560
The women's restroom is this way.

307
00:27:08,720 --> 00:27:10,280
Well…

308
00:27:10,360 --> 00:27:11,560
Yes?

309
00:27:12,280 --> 00:27:13,160
Never mind.

310
00:27:13,240 --> 00:27:14,480
Wait.

311
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:17,080
Just be honest with me.

312
00:27:19,120 --> 00:27:21,400
Do you need me to help
with something specific?

313
00:27:21,480 --> 00:27:23,080
Or…

314
00:27:24,200 --> 00:27:25,600
Hey, don't get pervy on me!

315
00:27:25,680 --> 00:27:27,000
Why are you insulting me?

316
00:27:27,080 --> 00:27:28,720
Just don't act all creepy with me.

317
00:27:28,800 --> 00:27:30,640
I'm not being creepy.

318
00:27:31,480 --> 00:27:33,280
You've got something on your shirt.

319
00:27:39,920 --> 00:27:41,320
Get away. Don't come any closer.

320
00:27:41,400 --> 00:27:42,960
Alright, I'll go back to work then.

321
00:27:43,720 --> 00:27:46,320
Wait!

322
00:27:47,160 --> 00:27:48,160
Fine!

323
00:27:49,840 --> 00:27:53,600
I need you to help me with something.

324
00:27:53,680 --> 00:27:55,200
Sure, tell me what you need.

325
00:27:56,600 --> 00:28:01,360
Since you're close with Mr. Sornrak,
I want to know his schedule.

326
00:28:01,440 --> 00:28:04,560
Where does he go and what does he do?

327
00:28:05,640 --> 00:28:08,040
- Sure, which day do you want?
- Every day.

328
00:28:08,880 --> 00:28:10,320
What do you need it for?

329
00:28:10,960 --> 00:28:12,360
It's none of your business.

330
00:28:12,440 --> 00:28:14,960
Sure, but you'll need
to have dinner with me once.

331
00:28:15,040 --> 00:28:16,320
Hey!

332
00:28:16,400 --> 00:28:17,360
What do you say?

333
00:28:17,440 --> 00:28:18,400
No!

334
00:28:19,000 --> 00:28:23,080
You can give me an answer later.
If you want Mr. Sornrak's schedule,

335
00:28:23,600 --> 00:28:26,160
you just have to have dinner with me.
It's that simple.

336
00:28:35,000 --> 00:28:37,160
MARIA DARATHONG

337
00:29:11,640 --> 00:29:17,000
<i>I want to sing, but I can't really sing</i>

338
00:29:23,280 --> 00:29:24,760
While you're here,

339
00:29:24,840 --> 00:29:27,600
don't go around flirting with every girl.

340
00:29:28,720 --> 00:29:30,040
You country fool!

341
00:29:30,880 --> 00:29:33,800
What's wrong, Chang?

342
00:29:33,880 --> 00:29:35,720
Nothing. Just that I don't like you.

343
00:29:37,280 --> 00:29:38,760
If I did something wrong,

344
00:29:39,480 --> 00:29:41,080
I'm sorry!

345
00:29:41,160 --> 00:29:42,280
Good.

346
00:29:43,520 --> 00:29:46,000
Learn to be polite with me.

347
00:29:52,360 --> 00:29:53,520
Sweet dreams, Chang.

348
00:29:55,160 --> 00:29:56,000
Manat.

349
00:29:58,600 --> 00:29:59,880
Sornrak's calling.

350
00:30:03,760 --> 00:30:05,920
At least you weren't hurt too badly.

351
00:30:06,720 --> 00:30:08,960
Dad, it was close, though.

352
00:30:09,040 --> 00:30:11,240
I was lucky that…

353
00:30:11,760 --> 00:30:14,280
these two helped me out

354
00:30:14,360 --> 00:30:17,080
and took me to the hospital.

355
00:30:17,160 --> 00:30:19,040
This is Chaiya and Manat.

356
00:30:19,720 --> 00:30:20,560
Hello.

357
00:30:21,160 --> 00:30:24,520
Hello. Thank you both so much.

358
00:30:24,600 --> 00:30:26,520
You're welcome, Mr. Singha.

359
00:30:26,600 --> 00:30:29,520
I heard you two are skilled
in fighting as well?

360
00:30:32,600 --> 00:30:34,200
Nothing special.

361
00:30:34,720 --> 00:30:38,640
They're YouTubers, Dad.
I had them help me out with my work,

362
00:30:38,720 --> 00:30:40,960
and they're also my personal bodyguards.

363
00:30:41,800 --> 00:30:42,800
Good, son.

364
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:46,480
Anyway, please take good care of my son.

365
00:30:47,600 --> 00:30:48,760
Of course.

366
00:30:48,840 --> 00:30:51,040
DARATHONG MUSIC

367
00:31:05,560 --> 00:31:06,800
Did you sleep well, Chang?

368
00:31:07,680 --> 00:31:08,760
Don't say anything.

369
00:31:09,280 --> 00:31:11,120
Let's go already.

370
00:31:11,200 --> 00:31:12,160
Let's go.

371
00:31:26,720 --> 00:31:29,080
Hod is following Sornrak.

372
00:31:29,600 --> 00:31:31,760
If anything happens to Sornrak,

373
00:31:31,840 --> 00:31:33,280
Singha won't just stand by.

374
00:31:34,760 --> 00:31:36,320
It's your job now, Khod.

375
00:31:36,920 --> 00:31:38,280
Get ready to handle Singha.

376
00:31:39,520 --> 00:31:40,680
Got it, Pleaw.

377
00:31:55,440 --> 00:31:56,960
Poona, let me help.

378
00:31:57,040 --> 00:31:59,240
It's okay, Teacher. It's not heavy.

379
00:31:59,320 --> 00:32:01,400
Where should we put this?

380
00:32:01,480 --> 00:32:06,160
In the conference room. The boss said
to clean and dust everything.

381
00:32:06,240 --> 00:32:07,400
This teddy bear too?

382
00:32:13,720 --> 00:32:15,440
I was going to find a place to wash it.

383
00:32:20,760 --> 00:32:22,400
Poona, did you see that?

384
00:32:23,800 --> 00:32:25,080
Yes, Teacher.

385
00:32:44,240 --> 00:32:46,200
Where are you taking the laundry, Poona?

386
00:32:46,280 --> 00:32:47,560
I'm going to iron it.

387
00:32:47,640 --> 00:32:50,160
Oh, can you wash it for me too?

388
00:32:50,240 --> 00:32:53,360
Sure, let me know what you need washed.

389
00:32:53,440 --> 00:32:55,040
The teddy bear inside.

390
00:32:56,960 --> 00:33:00,480
Leave it for now. I feel bad asking.
Don't worry about it, Poona.

391
00:33:07,600 --> 00:33:10,960
Quick, go into the room.
I'll keep an eye outside for you.

392
00:33:50,240 --> 00:33:51,320
Where is it?

393
00:33:51,400 --> 00:33:52,560
In the basket.

394
00:33:54,520 --> 00:33:56,080
Then quickly hide it in the car.

395
00:34:01,560 --> 00:34:03,240
They're acting suspicious.

396
00:34:04,400 --> 00:34:06,320
They must be stealing something.

397
00:34:06,960 --> 00:34:09,600
Miss Maria needs to know about this.

398
00:34:09,679 --> 00:34:11,040
Of course.

399
00:34:22,120 --> 00:34:23,040
Hey!

400
00:34:25,440 --> 00:34:27,400
Where are you taking the laundry?

401
00:34:27,480 --> 00:34:29,679
Uh, well…

402
00:34:29,760 --> 00:34:32,400
Poona washed the clothes,
but they're not dry.

403
00:34:32,480 --> 00:34:34,239
She's going to hang them
in the parking lot.

404
00:34:34,320 --> 00:34:36,520
Really? She looks suspicious.

405
00:34:37,920 --> 00:34:40,719
Like she's stealing something.

406
00:34:41,239 --> 00:34:42,520
I'm not stealing anything.

407
00:34:42,600 --> 00:34:45,159
If you're not stealing,
then what's hidden in the basket?

408
00:34:48,440 --> 00:34:50,719
Yeah, there's something

409
00:34:50,800 --> 00:34:52,440
tucked in the basket.

410
00:34:54,639 --> 00:34:55,760
Let's see what it is.

411
00:34:55,840 --> 00:34:57,240
That's enough!

412
00:34:57,320 --> 00:34:59,920
Who are you guys to interfere
with other people like this?

413
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:01,960
I'm an artist of the company.

414
00:35:02,480 --> 00:35:05,160
And I'm also part of Miss Maria's team.

415
00:35:05,240 --> 00:35:07,080
So I'm part of the company too.

416
00:35:07,600 --> 00:35:09,840
If you're innocent, just show us.

417
00:35:09,920 --> 00:35:11,960
- Don't come any closer.
- Take it from her!

418
00:35:12,640 --> 00:35:14,200
- Hey, stop!
- Give it to me.

419
00:35:14,280 --> 00:35:15,960
- Give it to me!
- Let it go!

420
00:35:16,040 --> 00:35:17,840
- Give it to me!
- No!

421
00:35:26,800 --> 00:35:28,120
Who took my teddy bear out?

422
00:35:34,080 --> 00:35:35,240
It's Poona.

423
00:35:35,320 --> 00:35:37,920
She stole your teddy bear, Mr. Singha.

424
00:35:38,000 --> 00:35:38,920
It's true.

425
00:35:41,200 --> 00:35:42,440
Don't accuse her of that.

426
00:35:42,520 --> 00:35:45,640
It's just an old teddy bear.
Why would she want to steal it?

427
00:35:47,080 --> 00:35:49,440
Yes, I didn't steal it.

428
00:35:50,240 --> 00:35:52,840
I just noticed some clothes
were gathering dust,

429
00:35:52,920 --> 00:35:55,920
so I decided to wash them,
including this teddy bear.

430
00:35:57,680 --> 00:35:58,920
Poona!

431
00:36:00,080 --> 00:36:01,360
Thank you so much.

432
00:36:01,440 --> 00:36:02,760
We were just joking.

433
00:36:02,840 --> 00:36:04,840
Didn't think you'd actually help
with the laundry.

434
00:36:08,360 --> 00:36:10,560
She didn't steal it, Mr. Singha.

435
00:36:10,640 --> 00:36:13,560
You asked us to clean the room,

436
00:36:13,640 --> 00:36:16,640
and we saw Poona
was about to wash the clothes,

437
00:36:16,720 --> 00:36:18,280
so we jokingly asked her to help.

438
00:36:18,360 --> 00:36:21,120
We didn't expect her to really do it.

439
00:36:25,280 --> 00:36:26,600
Does that mean

440
00:36:27,480 --> 00:36:29,280
you falsely accused Poona earlier?

441
00:36:31,680 --> 00:36:33,000
It wasn't me.

442
00:36:34,080 --> 00:36:38,400
It was Sophie. She falsely accused Poona.
I only heard it from her.

443
00:36:38,480 --> 00:36:40,000
Yes-- I mean, no!

444
00:36:40,080 --> 00:36:43,800
It wasn't me! I heard it from Joey!

445
00:36:43,880 --> 00:36:47,200
Yeah, that's right. I told Sophie--
Wait, are you serious?!

446
00:36:47,280 --> 00:36:48,920
Am I the one at fault now?

447
00:36:50,520 --> 00:36:52,120
Sophie, Joey.

448
00:36:52,200 --> 00:36:55,560
Next time, think carefully
about what you say.

449
00:36:55,640 --> 00:36:57,520
Don't just say things randomly.

450
00:36:59,000 --> 00:37:01,120
Look at what's happening to Poona
because of this.

451
00:37:02,360 --> 00:37:04,880
Poona, I'm really sorry.

452
00:37:04,960 --> 00:37:06,560
We misunderstood you.

453
00:37:06,640 --> 00:37:07,960
Sorry.

454
00:37:08,040 --> 00:37:11,000
Next time, don't misunderstand so easily.

455
00:37:11,560 --> 00:37:15,400
Poona's been washing clothes all day.
She's been working hard.

456
00:37:16,000 --> 00:37:16,840
Yeah.

457
00:37:16,920 --> 00:37:18,760
If you're done clearing this up,
you can go.

458
00:37:19,840 --> 00:37:23,720
Don't ever argue in front of the company
where people can see.

459
00:37:23,800 --> 00:37:26,040
If I find out who started it,

460
00:37:26,120 --> 00:37:27,960
I'll fire everyone involved.

461
00:37:30,600 --> 00:37:31,560
Wait.

462
00:37:31,640 --> 00:37:34,760
Can we argue
without anyone else seeing it?

463
00:37:36,280 --> 00:37:39,280
- Where would that be?
- Just asking.

464
00:37:41,800 --> 00:37:43,120
Mr. Singha.

465
00:37:44,440 --> 00:37:45,280
What is it?

466
00:37:47,360 --> 00:37:51,240
Let me wash this teddy bear for you.

467
00:38:24,840 --> 00:38:25,880
Actually, never mind.

468
00:38:27,400 --> 00:38:28,240
No need to wash it.

469
00:38:34,720 --> 00:38:36,440
What's going on? What happened?

470
00:38:37,640 --> 00:38:39,000
Nothing. Let's go.

471
00:38:48,040 --> 00:38:49,600
We'll head out now, Poona.

472
00:39:10,920 --> 00:39:13,720
I had the staff move things around
for cleaning today,

473
00:39:13,800 --> 00:39:15,320
so the room looks a bit empty.

474
00:39:16,000 --> 00:39:18,200
And how's Sornrak doing?

475
00:39:19,480 --> 00:39:22,360
He's recovered and is back to work.

476
00:39:23,360 --> 00:39:27,400
I think the thugs who attacked Sornrak

477
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:30,360
must be from Boss Noo's group.

478
00:39:30,440 --> 00:39:32,800
Why are they messing with my son?

479
00:39:34,800 --> 00:39:38,080
Those guys have a bad history.

480
00:39:38,840 --> 00:39:40,200
You need to be careful.

481
00:39:40,280 --> 00:39:44,440
They managed to get away that day,
but they'll definitely come back.

482
00:39:45,200 --> 00:39:46,560
Don't wait for them.

483
00:39:47,080 --> 00:39:48,520
We need to take action first.

484
00:39:48,600 --> 00:39:50,280
Alright.

485
00:39:50,360 --> 00:39:54,400
I'll have Chart take care of it,
but we'll need some money.

486
00:39:57,000 --> 00:39:57,840
I don't have any cash right now.

487
00:39:59,480 --> 00:40:03,240
I used it to buy raw materials
for the new batch of goods.

488
00:40:04,480 --> 00:40:07,320
I'm still negotiating for a deposit
from the clients.

489
00:40:07,400 --> 00:40:10,680
Then why not use
the singer promotion budget for now?

490
00:40:11,200 --> 00:40:13,040
I heard that

491
00:40:13,920 --> 00:40:17,480
Kamnan Pong signed off
on the budget for Poona's song.

492
00:40:23,240 --> 00:40:24,760
Poona's song budget?

493
00:40:26,320 --> 00:40:27,360
Yeah.

494
00:40:28,240 --> 00:40:30,320
Just hold off on her song for now

495
00:40:30,400 --> 00:40:32,680
and use the money to cover other things.

496
00:41:29,760 --> 00:41:30,800
What the hell?!

497
00:41:32,800 --> 00:41:35,040
- What do we do, Chaiya?
- Get Mr. Sornrak out of here! Go!

498
00:41:35,640 --> 00:41:37,440
Hurry! Go!

499
00:42:03,240 --> 00:42:05,760
Chang, call my dad!

500
00:42:08,280 --> 00:42:09,080
What's going on?

501
00:42:09,160 --> 00:42:11,400
Boss, Mr. Sornrak has been shot at.

502
00:42:12,280 --> 00:42:14,120
What? Shot at?

503
00:42:14,920 --> 00:42:16,000
Where is he now?

504
00:42:17,560 --> 00:42:19,080
Wait there. I'll rush over.

505
00:42:19,160 --> 00:42:20,280
What happened?

506
00:42:21,120 --> 00:42:22,360
Sornrak's been shot at.

507
00:42:22,960 --> 00:42:24,920
Hurry and tell Chit's group to come help.

508
00:42:32,240 --> 00:42:33,440
Hurry up!

509
00:42:35,200 --> 00:42:36,280
Hey, hold off.

510
00:42:37,200 --> 00:42:39,560
Let's wait until he's outside the company.

511
00:42:40,720 --> 00:42:42,920
There are too many security cameras here.

512
00:42:46,400 --> 00:42:47,400
Follow him!

513
00:43:04,160 --> 00:43:05,000
Chang, let's go!

514
00:43:06,120 --> 00:43:07,400
Mr. Sornrak, don't go!

515
00:43:08,560 --> 00:43:10,400
Follow him!

516
00:43:40,720 --> 00:43:42,120
Faster, Yak!

517
00:44:23,840 --> 00:44:25,200
It's definitely Boss Noo's men.

518
00:44:26,720 --> 00:44:27,760
We're not getting out of this.

519
00:44:33,440 --> 00:44:35,240
The team's here to help, Boss.

520
00:44:35,320 --> 00:44:37,040
Then hurry up and help Sornrak first. Go!

521
00:44:37,120 --> 00:44:38,120
Got it, Boss.

522
00:44:47,640 --> 00:44:48,800
Damn it, Chang!

523
00:44:53,000 --> 00:44:54,120
Stop!

524
00:45:05,640 --> 00:45:07,400
I told you to stay right there!

525
00:45:20,600 --> 00:45:23,880
Please, don't. No, please don't do this.

526
00:45:25,400 --> 00:45:26,480
Just die already!

527
00:45:27,120 --> 00:45:28,560
No! Don't!

528
00:45:30,440 --> 00:45:31,400
Mr. Sornrak!

529
00:45:42,400 --> 00:45:43,960
- No!
- Sornrak!

530
00:45:44,040 --> 00:45:46,040
- Are you alright?
- Dad!

531
00:45:47,120 --> 00:45:50,240
- Are you hurt?
- I'm fine, Dad.

532
00:45:51,640 --> 00:45:53,640
But why were they trying to kill me?

533
00:45:56,880 --> 00:45:58,200
They must be our competitors.

534
00:45:59,560 --> 00:46:01,600
From now on, you need to be extra careful.

535
00:46:02,440 --> 00:46:03,720
Yes, Dad.

536
00:46:19,080 --> 00:46:21,440
Are you okay, sir?

537
00:46:26,560 --> 00:46:27,720
They've already fled.

538
00:46:28,360 --> 00:46:30,280
How did you let this happen to my son?!

539
00:46:30,360 --> 00:46:32,280
If I was any later, my son would be dead!

540
00:46:33,200 --> 00:46:34,320
Sorry, Mr. Singha.

541
00:46:35,080 --> 00:46:38,200
We failed. We couldn't
keep up with Mr. Sornrak.

542
00:46:39,480 --> 00:46:42,760
But next time, don't run off like that.
It's dangerous.

543
00:46:42,840 --> 00:46:45,200
Wait, are you talking back to the boss?

544
00:46:46,000 --> 00:46:47,800
Enough, Chang.

545
00:46:47,880 --> 00:46:51,920
It's my fault. If I hadn't run,
I wouldn't be in this mess.

546
00:46:55,040 --> 00:46:56,240
Kitti.

547
00:46:57,120 --> 00:46:58,280
Who are they?

548
00:47:01,200 --> 00:47:03,080
Boss Noo's men.

549
00:47:04,440 --> 00:47:05,920
Boss Noo!

550
00:47:06,560 --> 00:47:07,480
Dad.

551
00:47:08,000 --> 00:47:10,920
Who is Boss Noo?
Why are they trying to kill me?

552
00:47:14,120 --> 00:47:15,360
They're thugs.

553
00:47:16,720 --> 00:47:18,280
Your career is taking off.

554
00:47:18,800 --> 00:47:22,040
They're jealous.
They don't want anyone to succeed.

555
00:47:23,320 --> 00:47:25,160
- But, Dad…
- Hey.

556
00:47:26,000 --> 00:47:27,160
We'll talk about this later.

557
00:47:28,960 --> 00:47:32,080
Don't ask too many questions
right now, okay?

558
00:47:32,600 --> 00:47:33,560
Okay, Dad.

559
00:47:37,960 --> 00:47:39,400
What are you doing?

560
00:47:39,480 --> 00:47:41,080
- Calling the police.
- No need!

561
00:47:52,120 --> 00:47:57,080
NEXT EPISODE

562
00:47:57,160 --> 00:47:58,880
Who sent you to hurt Mr. Sornrak that day?

563
00:47:59,720 --> 00:48:00,800
An amulet?

564
00:48:01,320 --> 00:48:03,840
Venerable Father Dang
from Sanandong Temple.

565
00:48:05,240 --> 00:48:08,320
I hope you achieve the fame you deserve,
Maria Darathong.

566
00:48:10,200 --> 00:48:11,320
Do you even realize…

567
00:48:12,400 --> 00:48:13,520
how cute you are?

568
00:48:16,040 --> 00:48:22,880
<i>Don't let anyone hug these shoulders</i>

569
00:48:22,960 --> 00:48:28,520
<i>Don't let anyone grab these hands</i>

570
00:48:29,120 --> 00:48:30,120
What the heck is going on here?

571
00:48:30,200 --> 00:48:32,560
<i>Don't let anyone kiss this forehead</i>

572
00:51:28,600 --> 00:51:32,600
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
